itemDescription: Master of Winchester College, Warden of New College, Oxford, and Vice-Chancellor of Oxford University

wikipedia_page.main: David Williams (15 October 1786, in Lasham, Hampshire – 22 March 1860, in New College, Oxford) was Master of Winchester College, Warden of New College, Oxford (1840–60), and Vice-Chancellor of Oxford University (1856–58).Williams is buried in the antechapel of New College chapel.
